Aufgabe 2:

1) rm:
    a) removes files and directories
    b) /usr/bin/rm
    c) rm filename
    d) unlink()

2) mv:
    a) move (rename) files
    b) /usr/bin/mv
    c) mv file1.txt file2.txt
    d) rename()

3) chmod:
    a) change file mods bits
    b) /usr/bin/chmod
    c) chmod 755 file.text          //[user, group, others] --> [ 4 for read, 2 for write, 1 for execute, 0 for no permission]
    d) chmod()

4) chown:
    a) change file owner and group
    b) /usr/bin/chown
    c) chown root /u --> change the owner of /u to root
    d) chown()

5) mkdir:
    a) make directories
    b) /usr/bin/mkdir
    c) mkdir Foldername
    d) mkdir()

6) rmdir:
    a) remove empty directories
    b) /usr/bin/rmdir
    c) rmdir Foldername
    d) rmdir()

7) kill:
    a) send a signal to a process to terminate
    b) /usr/bin/kill
    c) kill -9 <PID>
    d) kill()

8) ln:
    a) makes links between files
    b) /usr/bin/ln
    c) ln filename1 filename2
    d) link(), symlink()

9) sleep:
    a) delay for a specified amount of time
    b) /usr/bin/sleep
    c) sleep 5
    d) nanosleep(), clock_nanosleep()

10) wget:
    a) a network downloader for downloading directly from websites
    b) /usr/bin/wget
    c) wget <URL>
    d) socket(), connect(), recvfrom()